Learn. Adapt. Grow 🔄 

Entrepreneurship is a constant learning curve. Raghav Gandotra & Radhika Rajpal, Co-founders of PatchUp, share how embracing mistakes, building the right team and staying open to learning are key to success.

Key Takeaways from this episode of #BadhtaIndiaDekho:
✅ Admitting you don’t know something is the first step to learning. 📖
✅ Your team is your biggest asset—choose people who wear your brand with pride. 👏
✅ Growth requires continuous evolution—what got you here won’t get you there. 🚀

Watch now & tell us—what’s the best lesson you’ve learned on your journey? Drop your thoughts in the comments! 👇

#BadhtaIndiaDekho #PatchUp #StartupMindset #Leadership #GrowthMindset #Entrepreneurship #LearnAndGrow #BuildingTeams #HustleCulture #Innovation

Entrepreneurial Spirit Since 2nd Grade! 💡

Who knew a 100-year calendar could spark a business idea? 🤯 As a 2nd grader, Radhika Rajpal photocopied and sold calendars to her classmates—making a 50% profit! 💰

Fast forward to today, and she’s building PatchUp, a game-changing health startup! 🚀 

Catch this fun & inspiring conversation on #BadhtaIndiaDekho with Debojit Sen! 🎙️
